<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When adding a second language to Zend_Translate the first set language will stay set.</p>

<p>If you set several languages the best fitting language should be selected.</p>

<p>f.e.</p>

<p>Browser reports 'de' =&gt; 100&amp;, 'fr' =&gt; 80%, 'en' =&gt; 50%</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$locale = new Zend_Translate('csv', 'myfile.csv', 'hu');
$locale-&gt;addLanguage('myfile2.csv', 'en');
$locale-&gt;addLanguage('myfile3.csv','fr');
</code></pre>

<p>actual the language will be set to 'hu'
The user would have to manually set the language with setLocale() to fr...</p>

<p>after the change the language will be automatically set to the best fitting one, in our case 'fr'.</p>

<p>If the user sets manually a language with setLocale() any further addLanguage would result in no change on the language.</p>

<p>The best fitting locale could also be set if the "locale" is set to "auto".</p>

